    <Fragment is:raw>
      <h4>Code từ OpenHarness</h4> <pre><code><span class="kw">from</span> enum
      <span class="kw">import</span> Enum <span class="kw">class</span> <span
      class="type">HookEvent</span>(Enum): SESSION_START = <span
      class="str">"session_start"</span> SESSION_END = <span
      class="str">"session_end"</span> PRE_COMPACT = <span
      class="str">"pre_compact"</span> POST_COMPACT = <span
      class="str">"post_compact"</span> PRE_TOOL_USE = <span
      class="str">"pre_tool_use"</span> POST_TOOL_USE = <span
      class="str">"post_tool_use"</span> <span class="kw">class</span> <span
      class="type">HookType</span>(Enum): COMMAND = <span
      class="str">"command"</span> <span class="com"># exec shell command, check
      exit code</span> PROMPT = <span class="str">"prompt"</span> <span
      class="com"># LLM judges payload vs policy</span> HTTP = <span
      class="str">"http"</span> <span class="com"># POST payload to
      webhook</span> AGENT = <span class="str">"agent"</span> <span
      class="com"># spawn subagent for decision</span> <span
      class="kw">class</span> <span class="type">HookExecutor</span>: <span
      class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">execute</span>(self, event:
      HookEvent, payload: dict) -&gt; HookResult: self._maybe_reload() <span
      class="com"># hot-reload when files changed</span> blocked, reasons =
      <span class="kw">False</span>, [] <span class="kw">for</span> hook <span
      class="kw">in</span> self._hooks_for(event): res = <span
      class="kw">await</span> hook.run(payload) reasons.append(res.message)
      <span class="kw">if</span> res.blocked: blocked = <span
      class="kw">True</span> <span class="kw">if</span> hook.type ==
      HookType.COMMAND: <span class="kw">break</span> <span class="com">#
      short-circuit for command hooks</span> <span class="kw">return</span>
      HookResult(blocked=blocked, reason=<span class="str">";
      "</span>.join(reasons)) <span class="kw">class</span> <span
      class="type">HookReloader</span>: <span class="str">"""Watch hook file
      mtime; reload config when modified."""</span> <span class="kw">def</span>
      <span class="fn">maybe_reload</span>(self): <span class="kw">for</span>
      path, old_mtime <span class="kw">in</span> <span
      class="kw">list</span>(self._mtimes.items()): new_mtime =
      path.stat().st_mtime <span class="kw">if</span> new_mtime != old_mtime:
      log.info(<span class="str">"reloading hooks from %s"</span>, path)
      self._hooks = self._parse(path) self._mtimes[path] =
      new_mtime</code></pre> <div class="why"><strong>Tại sao quan
      trọng:</strong> Hook lifecycle 6 event là đủ cho hầu hết policy scenarios:
      session bound (SESSION_START/END), compaction tracking (PRE/POST_COMPACT),
      tool enforcement (PRE/POST_TOOL_USE). 4 hook types cho phép user chọn cơ
      chế: command = simple shell, prompt = LLM-based policy, HTTP = remote
      SIEM, agent = sophisticated reasoning. Hot reload qua mtime watch — sửa
      <code>hooks.yaml</code> không cần restart session.</div> <h4>Code example
      (generic)</h4> <pre><code><span class="kw">import</span> asyncio,
      subprocess <span class="kw">from</span> enum <span
      class="kw">import</span> Enum <span class="kw">class</span> <span
      class="type">HookEvent</span>(Enum): PRE_TOOL = <span
      class="str">"pre_tool"</span>; POST_TOOL = <span
      class="str">"post_tool"</span> <span class="kw">class</span> <span
      class="type">CommandHook</span>: <span class="kw">def</span> <span
      class="fn">__init__</span>(self, cmd): self.cmd = cmd <span
      class="kw">async def</span> <span class="fn">run</span>(self, payload):
      proc = <span class="kw">await</span> asyncio.create_subprocess_shell(
      self.cmd, stdin=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE, stdout=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE,
      stderr=asyncio.subprocess.PIPE, ) out, err = <span class="kw">await</span>
      proc.communicate(json.dumps(payload).encode()) <span
      class="kw">return</span> {<span class="str">"blocked"</span>:
      proc.returncode != <span class="num">0</span>, <span
      class="str">"reason"</span>: err.decode()} <span class="kw">class</span>
      <span class="type">HookExecutor</span>: <span class="kw">def</span> <span
      class="fn">__init__</span>(self, hooks_by_event): self.hooks =
      hooks_by_event <span class="kw">async def</span> <span
      class="fn">fire</span>(self, event, payload): <span class="kw">for</span>
      h <span class="kw">in</span> self.hooks.get(event, []): r = <span
      class="kw">await</span> h.run(payload) <span class="kw">if</span> r[<span
      class="str">"blocked"</span>]: <span class="kw">return</span> r <span
      class="kw">return</span> {<span class="str">"blocked"</span>: <span
      class="kw">False</span>}</code></pre>
    </Fragment>
    <ProsCons
      pros={[
        "6 lifecycle events covers compaction + tool + session",
        "Hot reload — no session restart",
        "4 hook types — flexible (simple → sophisticated)",
